20
00:07:44,798 --> 00:07:46,498
VARIETY:
WHO'S THAT GIRL?

21
00:09:13,627 --> 00:09:15,130
KINOGRAPH STUDIOS

22
00:09:56,266 --> 00:09:58,867
"Listen up! Three girls
who can dance !"

23
00:10:35,579 --> 00:10:37,579
"The name's Miller.
Peppy Miller !"

24
00:11:29,193 --> 00:11:31,693
"Clifton, go to the jewelry store. Get something
nice for my wife. To make it up to her."

25
00:12:21,328 --> 00:12:24,828
"With all your nonsense, they don't
mention our movie until page 5 !"

26
00:14:02,732 --> 00:14:04,832
"Where are you going, Miss?
We have a picture to shot."

27
00:19:19,380 --> 00:19:22,780
"If you want to be an actress, you
need to have something the others don't."

28
00:21:45,807 --> 00:21:48,307
And Peppy Miller
as Miss Isadora

29
00:21:59,498 --> 00:22:01,998
1929

30
00:22:46,533 --> 00:22:48,133
"I have something to
show you."

31
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:56,550
"May I have my chair?!"

32
00:22:57,947 --> 00:22:59,847
"Hey, you're not Napoleon.
You're just an extra!"

33
00:23:03,328 --> 00:23:04,928
SOUND TEST
Constance Gray
in Romeo & Juliet

34
00:24:02,324 --> 00:24:04,124
"Don't laugh, George!
That's the future."

35
00:24:06,095 --> 00:24:08,295
"If that's the future,
you can have it!"

36
00:27:01,708 --> 00:27:04,708
Kinograph Studios Stop All Silent Productions
To Work Exclusively On Talkies

37
00:27:51,779 --> 00:27:54,479
"You and I belong to another era,
George. The world is talking now."

38
00:27:59,276 --> 00:28:02,028
"People want new faces,
talking faces.'

39
00:28:09,049 --> 00:28:11,949
"I wish it wasn't like this, but the public wants
fresh meat and the public is never wrong."

40
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:24,620
"I'm the one people come to see.
They never needed to hear me!"

41
00:28:31,012 --> 00:28:34,812
"Make your talking movies. I'll make a great
movie. And it's not like I need you for that!"

42
00:28:41,463 --> 00:28:43,563
THE NEW FACES
of KINOGRAPH

43
00:28:45,346 --> 00:28:46,846
Peppy Miller

44
00:28:48,660 --> 00:28:50,160
"Fresh meat..."

45
00:29:26,999 --> 00:29:29,699
"What a coincidence, I was just thinking
about you. I signed with Kinograph!"

46
00:29:35,969 --> 00:29:38,269
"Maybe now we'll do
another picture together!"

47
00:30:37,004 --> 00:30:38,004
"Toys!"

48
00:33:24,189 --> 00:33:25,589
"I'm not a puppet, I'm an artist!"

49
00:33:25,992 --> 00:33:27,392
"Talkies are not serious"
for George Valentin

50
00:33:59,262 --> 00:34:00,796
"We have to talk, George."

51
00:34:11,632 --> 00:34:13,332
"Why do you refuse to talk?"

52
00:34:36,961 --> 00:34:38,461
"I'm unhappy, George."

53
00:34:40,502 --> 00:34:42,602
"So are millions of us."

54
00:35:40,944 --> 00:35:42,989
"Your movie doesn't come out
until tomorrow and you're,

55
00:35:42,990 --> 00:35:45,294
already Hollywood's new sweetheart!
How do you explain that?"

56
00:35:52,183 --> 00:35:54,433
"I don't know. Maybe because I talk
and the audience can hear me."

57
00:36:00,963 --> 00:36:04,413
"People are tired of old actors mugging
at the camera to be understood."

58
00:36:17,460 --> 00:36:20,310
"Out with the old, in with the new.
Make way for the young!"

59
00:36:22,721 --> 00:36:24,071
"That's the life!"

60
00:36:42,876 --> 00:36:44,226
"I've made way for you."

61
00:37:16,048 --> 00:37:17,698
STOCK MARKET
CRASH

62
00:37:30,961 --> 00:37:32,911
"It looks like we've gone bust."

63
00:37:40,712 --> 00:37:43,262
"Unless the movie is a big hit..."

64
00:41:26,693 --> 00:41:28,643
"Hello. I wanted to
talk to you. I..."

65
00:41:30,660 --> 00:41:32,460
"I just saw Tears of Love."

66
00:41:34,927 --> 00:41:36,727
"And now want a refund?"

67
00:41:43,033 --> 00:41:44,683
"Not too much mugging?"

68
00:41:51,681 --> 00:41:55,581
"No. I'm sorry about last night.
I didn't mean what I said..."

69
00:42:00,857 --> 00:42:03,107
"But you were right.
Make way for the young..."

70
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:18,080
"It's an honor to meet you.
My father is a big fan."

71
00:42:25,236 --> 00:42:27,336
"Ok. We're going now.
I'll call you soon."

72
00:42:38,651 --> 00:42:41,051
"Take me home.
I want to be alone."

73
00:45:57,086 --> 00:45:59,786
"How long has it been
since I last paid you, Clifton?"

74
00:46:02,132 --> 00:46:03,482
"One year, sir."

75
00:46:26,927 --> 00:46:28,577
"You're fired."

76
00:46:39,840 --> 00:46:41,790
"I'm not kidding, Clifton.
You're fired."

77
00:46:54,475 --> 00:46:56,875
"Keep the car. And find
yourself another job."

78
00:47:01,018 --> 00:47:02,968
"I don't want another job."

79
00:48:09,865 --> 00:48:12,565
TO-NIGHT AUCTION SALE
Famed Hollywood Actor: George Valentin

80
00:49:23,608 --> 00:49:25,558
"Congratulations! It's all sold,
you've got nothing left!"

81
00:51:00,387 --> 00:51:02,637
1932

82
00:53:28,565 --> 00:53:30,665
"Excuse me, may
I trouble you one moment?"

83
00:53:43,918 --> 00:53:45,868
"If anly he could talk!"

84
00:54:29,849 --> 00:54:31,799
"Look what's become of you..."

85
00:54:34,250 --> 00:54:37,100
"You've been stupid!
You've been proud!"

86
00:54:52,949 --> 00:54:54,299
"GET BACK HERE,
YOU LOSER!!!"

87
00:58:13,898 --> 00:58:15,548
"Oh my God! That's
George Valentin!"

88
00:58:20,255 --> 00:58:21,305
"I'll get my car!"

89
00:58:27,015 --> 00:58:29,115
"I'll say one thing, he
owes his life to that dog!"

90
00:59:00,857 --> 00:59:03,107
"We're ready. Go get
Miss Miller."

91
01:00:11,243 --> 01:00:13,193
"He's out of danger.
He needs rest now."

92
01:00:23,465 --> 01:00:26,615
"He was clutching this. It was
hard to get it away from him."

93
01:00:56,964 --> 01:00:59,514
"You think he could
rest at my house?"

94
01:02:44,318 --> 01:02:47,468
"I have to be on the set at nine o'clock.
We're shooting a very important scene."

95
01:03:20,238 --> 01:03:23,238
"Just think of it! *Sparkle of Love*,
starring George Valentin and Peppy Miller!"

96
01:03:38,472 --> 01:03:40,872
"George is a silent movie
actor. He's a nobody now."

97
01:03:49,140 --> 01:03:50,640
"What are you doing?"

98
01:03:54,586 --> 01:03:56,386
"I won't work anymore.
It's either him or me."

99
01:04:05,247 --> 01:04:07,947
"What I mean is, it's him AND
me! Or it's neither of us!"

100
01:04:15,675 --> 01:04:17,925
"Hey, I'm blackmailing
you! Get it?"

101
01:04:41,038 --> 01:04:42,838
"All right, send him
the damn screenplay."

102
01:05:14,321 --> 01:05:16,421
"I work for Miss Miller now."

103
01:05:21,157 --> 01:05:22,807
"Once again, she's
looking out for you."

104
01:05:49,789 --> 01:05:53,239
"Beware of your pride, if I may say so sir.
 Miss Miller is a good person, believe me."

105
01:11:08,817 --> 01:11:10,317
"CLIFTON!"

106
01:13:43,045 --> 01:13:45,145
"BANG!"

107
01:14:11,855 --> 01:14:15,905
"I feel so bad. I only wanted to
help you, take care of you..."

108
01:14:44,411 --> 01:14:46,811
"If only you would let
me help you, George Valentin."

109
01:14:51,096 --> 01:14:53,946
"It's impossible, Peppy. I'm washed up.
No one wants to see me speak."

110
01:15:00,079 --> 01:15:02,479
"There is one thing we
could try. Trust me."

